ntioning the world. Source: Ta\u0304ri\u0304kh Dimashq 5\/291 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u062f\u064e\u0627\u0648\u064f\u062f\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":4098,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/04\/ahmad-sunnah-tafseer-quran\/","url_meta":{"origin":32846,"position":2},"title":"Ahmad on Tafsir: The Sunnah is exegesis, explanation of Quran","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 4, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Fadl ibn Ziyad reported: I heard Ahmad Ibn Hanbal, may Allah have mercy on him, respond to a question on the opinion that the Sunnah overrules the Quran. Ahmad said, \u201cI do not dare say that. Rather, the Sunnah is the explanation of the Book and its clarification.\u201d Source: al-Bah\u0323r\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19573,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/07\/25\/ahmad-sunnah-act-fiqh-hadith\/","url_meta":{"origin":32846,"position":3},"title":"Ahmad on Sunnah: Not act on hadith until authenticated, understood","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 25, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn al-Qayyim reported: Abdullah ibn Ahmad said, \u201cI asked my father Ahmad ibn Hanbal about a man who has books, within which are the sayings of the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and the companions and the followers, but he cannot distinguish weak and rejected narrations,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25304,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/10\/22\/ahmad-follow-sunnah\/","url_meta":{"origin":32846,"position":4},"title":"Ahmad on Sunnah: Do not blindly follow me, follow Hadith","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 22, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abdul Barr reported: Imam Ahmad ibn Hanbal, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cAl-Awza\u2019i had opinions, Malik had opinions, Sufyan al-Thawri had opinions. Each of them had opinions, and it is all the same to me. Indeed, the proof is only in the narrations.\u201d In another narration, Imam\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25509,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/01\/wudu-fingers-through-beard\/","url_meta":{"origin":32846,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Running fingers through thick beard in ablution","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 1, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Uthman ibn Affan reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would run his fingers through his beard during ablution. Al-Tirmidhi said, \"According to this, the majority of the people of knowledge among the companions of the Prophet, and those after them, hold the opinion that fingers should be\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u06